FBIS4-55987 "dreeu101_k_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 CROATIA Tudjman Accepts Principles of Bosnia Mediators Tudjman Accepts Principles of Bosnia Mediators LD2405211294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 24 May 94 LD2405211294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Croatian President Dr. Franjo Tudjman received in the Presidential Palace this evening a delegation of countries whose diplomatic envoys make up the contact group for Bosnia-Herzegovina. French Ambassador Henri Marie-Chenu, British Ambassador Brian Sparrow, Belgian Ambassador Frans Hintjens, Aleksandr Grishchenko, deputy head of the Russian diplomatic mission, and German Charge d'Affaires Claude Robert Elner informed President Tudjman about conclusions reached at a meeting in Geneva yesterday by ministers of foreign affairs of the countries whose diplomatic envoys make up the contact group for Bosnia-Herzegovina. They handed President Tudjman a letter which the ministers of the contact group had sent to Alija Izetbegovic, president of the Bosnia-Herzegovina presidency, Kresimir Zubak, representative of the Bosnian Croats, and Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, containing the principles that the contact group is going to follow to halt the hostilities in Bosnia-Herzegovina. President Tudjman said he agreed with these principles and promised to exert his influence so that the negotiating sides should accept these principles and new measures for the resolution of the Bosnia-Herzegovina crisis.
